section.section:
The insurer may make a payment under paragraph (1) of this subsection only if:
within the period stated in the policy, which may not be less than 30 days after the death of the insured, the beneficiary designated in the policy does not make a claim under the policy or does not surrender the policy with proof of death;
the beneficiary is the estate of the insured;
the beneficiary is a minor;
the beneficiary dies before the insured; or
the beneficiary is not legally competent to give a valid release.
